30/01/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva said Thursday (29 January) that Macedonia plans to submit its formal bid for EU accession on 26 February. 
The application would be handed to the Irish presidency of the EU during Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski's visit to Dublin. 
A campaign in support of the bid would be launched with a declaration by Macedonia's assembly.
In other news Thursday, the EU police mission Proxima began deploying its staff in Tetovo and Kumanovo regional police offices. 
Personnel will monitor police reforms and assist in promoting integrated border management. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 30/01/04; MIA, AFP - 29/01/04)
